===Noun===
{{wikipediapar|ventricle (heart)}}
'''ventricle''' (''plural'' '''ventricles'')

# {{anatomy}} A small [[cavity]] or [[chamber]] in an [[organ]] of the [[body]]; especially a  chamber of the [[heart]]. In higher [[vertebrate]]s, the left ventricle receives arterial blood from the left [[atrium]] and pumps it into the [[aorta]], and the right ventricle receives venous blood from the right [[atrium]] and pumps it into the pulmonary artery. 

